loc: Nango, Seta River, Otsu City, Shiga Prefecture
rmk:
Rare wintering individual (in well observed cases, this species is rarer than
Ficedula parva in at least in this part of Japan).
The bird was photographed the day before by a different observer
and I recorded the voice today.  Although the photos have not yet been
closely examined for species identification, the voice clearly indicates
Ficedula albicilla.  On my photographs, uppertail coverts were dark.
Due to the difficult condition, the bill was not clearly photographed.
Later on, the initial photographs became available and the species
has also been confirmed (the lower mandible does not have a color
similar to that in F. parva; uppertail coverts are black).
A male, passage migrant, with also in background  a Chinese Francolin
